# Generic assignments without a distro-specific scope

# Distros pecific matches

# Debian

@assignment graphical-installer-allows-selection-of-many-packages (many-choices-gui) to debian positive;

# Ubuntu

@assignment many-preselections-ok (many-preselections) to ubuntu positive;

# For Ubuntu, the installation process for desktop editions is implemented using a GUI setup. This setup gives basic options (such as hostname etc), but has a predefined selection of software to be installed.
@assignment default-installer-is-gui-not-commandline-setup (commandline-setup) to ubuntu negative;
@assignment installer-adds-a-preselection-of-software (many-choices-gui) to ubuntu negative;

